Question: By when must originator institutions notify the ECB of an intended
  significant risk transfer in a securitisation transaction?
Example answer: Originator institutions that have initiated or are considering
  initiating the process of structuring a securitisation transaction
  for which they intend to recognise a significant risk transfer or to
  apply for permission under the CRR should notify the ECB at least
  three months in advance of the expected closing date of the
  transaction. Originator institutions should also provide the final
  version of the documentation no later than 15 days after the closing
  date of the transaction. (ECB Supervisory Manual, page 96)
