Question: When are NCAs expected to submit notifications to the ECB regarding
  LSIs, particularly high-impact or high-risk ones?
Example answer: Notifications are official, written documentation formally submitted
  by the NCAs to the ECB when specific circumstances arise, and in
  relation to high-impact and/or high-risk LSIs, NCAs are expected to
  submit a notification to the ECB at the early stages of any material
  supervisory procedures and/or material draft supervisory decisions.
  In accordance with predefined criteria, NCAs must also notify the
  ECB in the event of any financial deterioration in individual LSIs,
  regardless of their classification, and for the annual and semi-
  annual ex post reporting. (ECB Supervisory Manual, pages 113–114)
