Question: What activities, at a minimum, must the ongoing monitoring of internal
  models include each year?
Example answer: At a minimum, ongoing model monitoring should include on an annual
  basis: an assessment of the institution's compliance with the legal
  requirements, supervisory conditions, limitations and obligations
  imposed in ECB decisions on model approvals, as well as compliance
  with implementation plans and other supervisory measures; where
  appropriate, an analysis of back-testing results and time-series
  analysis for institutions authorised to use internal models for
  market risk; an analysis of internal model validations; where
  appropriate, an assessment of the outcomes of the annual
  benchmarking process; an assessment of non-material model changes
  and extensions; and where appropriate, an assessment of other
  internal reports on the internal model, with at least one
  supervisory meeting per institution per year included. (ECB
  Supervisory Manual, page 92)
