  the identification of potential topics is coordinated by the
  Directorate Supervisory Strategy and Risk in liaison with other SSM
  stakeholders such as DGs, JSTs, NCA horizontal divisions and
  international bodies. As the second line of defence, D/SSR conducts
  thematic reviews that aim to support the Supervisory Board to steer
  European banking supervision in line with the agreed risk priorities
  and to monitor the quality and effects of supervisory activities,
  whether at the JST or horizontal level. (ECB Supervisory Manual,
